body:
### What happened?

There is inconsistent capitalization for tooltips for the buttons on some pages:
      -  All Schools (Add New School, Edit School, Export All Schools to Excel buttons)
      - Finance General (Edit Cost Share, Export to Excel, Edit In-Kind Expense buttons)
      - Meals and Transport (Edit button)
 The rest of the system has each word in the tooltip capitalized, so to keep consistency throughout the system, all the tooltips should have the same capitalization.

title: Maddocks PTO Calculations Fix
body:
- Issue: #385 fixed. Volunteer should be able to utilize leftover PTO time based on PTO Earned+Start. The user cannot enter a number greater than this. 
- Major functionality change: PTO Eligibility. Before, setting Eligible -> Not Eligible would remove all PTO Eligibility and PTO Used up until the current month and year. After reviewing the Capstone Excel PtoStipend sheet, this may not be the direction the system wants to go. Based on the Excel sheets, some volunteers may be eligible for only a single month or vice versa. To counter this, setting Eligible -> Ineligible will set all future records to not eligible. And keep the eligibility status and PTO used for all the previous months. Setting Ineligible -> Eligible will function similarly. 
- Due to this change, PTO Start and End will be adjusted throughout the year if any changes in eligibility occur. If the volunteer is ineligible for PTO, they cannot accrue any PTO time. However, they can still use PTO time earned from PREVIOUS months when they were eligible.

body: ### What happened? The PTO ended is how much PTO you ended with last month, so isn't that PTO earned? I think we can just use PTO Accumulated (for pto earned YTD), PTO earned this month, and PTO used. title: Implement Persistence of Volunteer Selection across pages
body:
- When a volunteer is selected on a volunteer page, the selection will be reflected on another page.

**Current Bugs**
- The persistence is not implemented on ChildAssignments due to ongoing work on the page. I have let @ChristopherWashburn know about this and gave him the code to add once he merges this PR with his own branch. 
- ActivityLog can change the selected volunteer for other pages, but not the other way around. Example of this: Selecting a volunteer on Activity Log will update General, Demographics, and Financials. Selecting a volunteer on any page will NOT update the selection on Activity Log. The issue stems from the combobox.SelectedIndex being reset to null (-1), but I do not understand why this is happening. My only guess is that the binding is set to an object and not a nullable int. I sent @T-Moody a message about this to get his input. 

**Other Minor Changes**
- changed the styling of the volunteer combobox on volunteer demographics to match every other page
- added the option to clear the combobox selection
- added a null check in PopulateVolunteerInfo on volunteer demographics because it kept crashing if the selection was cleared on any other page

title: Maddocks volunteer financials final
body:
My apologies because this was a simple fix and a huge mistake on my part. Essentially, I accidently removed the UI update method call on my last pull request for the Refresh button.  A large amount of the issues that were occurring was due to this removal. My apologies for testing a broken page without that method call. 

Regarding the Refresh button functionality, the data is meant to get updated every time the user 'Saves' their changes. The Refresh button is strictly for any volunteer changes made outside of the page. Hitting this button won't do any calculations, unless I am mistaken on the purpose of this button. 

**- Issue 1: Inputting a valid number, and then pressing enter what a normal workflow would look like it says invalid number..**
	- Unsure how to tackle this issue since 'Enter' would have to correspond to a button on the screen. There is a property call for this but it's unable to save the current data context. I'll keep working on this, but for right now, it won't display any errors. 
**- Issue 2: We then try to add some valid hours with a volunteer and it won't let me, since I didn't fill out all the information. Which should just default to 0 like they are displayed before editing. So that way I can simply add hours.**
	- Biggest change to the page is that if no financial record exists, e.g. none for November 2023, a record will be immediately added and pushed to the database. As well as the page will update it's PTO Start, End and YTD. Before, the page displayed 0's as an indicator no record is found and made the page really confusing. That was an oversight on my end. 
**- Issue 3: Then when adding valid numbers, upon leaving the text box the border is still red, making me think that I input invalid numbers**
	- Changed in which a valid keystroke will remove the red border. An invalid keystroke will display red. 
**- Issue 4: Then when we have inputted valid info, it doesn't update any of the calculated values.**
	- That's my mistake. I accidently got rid of my UI update call.
**- Issue 5: Nor is this valid data persisted to the next month.**
	- It should be persisting now. 
**- Issue 6: Then when editing the hours back to 0, nothing gets recalculated, like the YTD hours and PTO earned, which is 60, when I only worked 40 hours?**
	- Due to my mistake as before. The data was getting changed in the DB but I accidently removed the UI update call. 
**- Issue 7: Then when I reload the volunteer page it doesn't update, but this data should be updated when I save the updates.**
	- The Reload/Refresh button is only for outside volunteer changes for the page. Like, volunteer was added or deleted. 
**- Issue 8: Also I am not sure why I earned 60 PTO hours when I worked 40, and then this calculated data is not persisted throughout other months**
	- The volunteer worked 40 regular hours and the PTO rate is currently 1.5. That equites to 60 PTO earned. The only fix I can think of for this is not to allow the PTO Earned to exceed the regular hours worked. 
**- Issue 9: Also while using the PTO, the start and end for PTO are automatically populated, but this also decreases the amount of PTO used, so we lose pto while not redeeming it?**
	- PTO earned and used are month-to-month values, and do not accrue over time. PTO start and end represent any form of rollback values. PTO used may be decreasing due to the PTO earned getting changed. This only occurs if the used exceeds the amount earned. A volunteer should never be able to use more PTO hours than they have currently earned.

title: [Bug]: Finance / FY and GY tabs - System Crashed while changing date range multiple times
body:
### What happened?

It appears that the system crashed and froze while changing the date range multiple times. As for what was expected to happen, the application should have been able to handle the user's request to change the date range without any issues, and the system should have continued to function normally. However, it seems that the application was unable to handle the multiple requests, causing it to crash and freeze.

### Steps to reproduce the issue

### To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:

1. Go to the Finance tab in the application.
2. Select the Fiscal Year/Grant Year tab.
3. Click on the "Select Grant Date Range" option.
4. Choose any start and end date range.
5. Repeat steps 4 multiple times, selecting different date ranges.

After repeating these steps, the application may encounter issues such as slowing down or becoming unresponsive, or it may crash or freeze altogether.

It's important to note that the issue may not occur every time the steps are repeated, and it may depend on factors such as the amount of data being entered, the performance of the server, or other variables. Therefore, it may be necessary to repeat the steps multiple times to observe the issue consistently.

### Expected Result

When following the steps to select a grant date range in the Finance tab of the application, I would expect the system to apply the filter and display the corresponding financial data for the selected date range.

I would also expect the system to handle multiple requests to select different date ranges without encountering any issues, such as slow response times, crashes, or freezes. The application should be able to process the user's requests smoothly and efficiently, allowing the user to filter the data as needed to perform their tasks.

### Actual Result

When following the steps to select a grant date range in the Finance tab of the application, the system encountered issues such as slow response times, crashes, or freezes.

title: Login screen database settings dialog, appsettings secrets removal, database startup checks.
body:
**Important: This change will remove the current connection string functionality.** You will need to launch the application in order to set the database settings. The first time the application is launched, the database settings dialog will show. You will enter your settings and they will be saved and the application will launch as usual. If you ever need to update the settings, you can click the button in the bottom right corner and modify the settings. The settings will only save if they are a valid connection to the database. Once the settings are modified, the application will need to be restarted. 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7833468/229273511-8d6b3e7d-12af-4ab1-9b3b-0719265833bd.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7833468/229273543-891cf7d8-a010-4a3a-a95f-fabb64209b11.png)


If the database connection fails, a message will show and prompt the user to modify the database credentials. If the user does not add working credentials, the application will not start.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7833468/229273396-b62c4f50-da09-4f58-8413-c6fa9a308af2.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7833468/229273415-548f44de-5c92-474e-9a2c-4a3991367262.png)


If the database credentials have never been setup, the user will be prompted to connect to a database (this will save their database settings here: (`C:\Users\<user>\AppData\Local\C_FGMS.UI\C_FGMS.UI_Url_<some random garbage>`\1.0.0.0\user.config, username and password are encrypted)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7833468/229273441-0aa726f5-d70e-45bd-aea0-2d025e6a100b.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7833468/229273454-dd85e30b-a1ac-4954-9d2c-f10f47413b57.png)


If the software detects that there are migrations to be applied, it will notify the user and give them the option to apply migrations or exit the application.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7833468/229273628-7ee167bb-b574-49fe-a368-4b4d3e77f755.png)
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7833468/229273650-27412120-6e35-4fab-ac7d-af26823ee2f3.png)

title: [Bug]: Application Crash Upon Saving Empty Volunteer in General Tab
body:
### What happened?

After inputting blank user input in the edit mode and attempting to save it, the application completely crashes.

### Steps to reproduce the issue

- Open the application and navigate to the "Volunteers" tab and then navigate the "General" tab.
- Click on the "Edit" button to make changes to the information.
- Leave the "Volunteer Name" field blank.
- Make any other desired changes to the information.
- Click on the "Save" button to save the changes.
- The application crashes and an error message appears.to 

### Expected Result

If the "Volunteer Name" field is left blank when attempting to save changes in the "General" tab, the application should display an alert or warning message stating that the field is required and cannot be left empty. The user should be prompted to enter a volunteer name before they can successfully save the changes. This would prevent the application from crashing and provide a better user experience.

### Actual Result

When attempting to save changes in the "General" tab without selecting a volunteer name, the application encounters a System.NullReferenceException error. The error message states that an object reference was not set to an instance of an object. The error occurs in the VolunteerGeneral.xaml.cs file at line 60, specifically in the btnFinish_Click() method. This means that there is a programming error in the code that is causing the application to crash.

### Relevant log output

```shell
System.NullReferenceException
  HResult=0x80004003
  Message=Object reference not set to an instance of an object.
  Source=System.Private.CoreLib
  StackTrace:
   at System.Runtime.CompilerServices.CastHelpers.Unbox(Void* toTypeHnd, Object obj)
   at C_FGMS.UI.VolunteerGeneral.btnFinish_Click(Object sender, RoutedEventArgs e) in C:\Users\rakib\Capstone-FGMS\FGMS\C_FGMS.UI\VolunteerGeneral.xaml.cs:line 60
```


### Environment

Windows 11

_No response_

### What happened?

Unless you specifically type "No" or "Yes" for the status, it will just revert back to the previous status upon restart of the app. So, it won't let you know that you are wrong either it will just delete all your work.

The idea is that you can pick between two states yes or no, not manually type this. And this should be persisted.

title: Started adding in pub/sub impl. for entity change events.
body:
Added a system to the project to handle notifying subscribers when entities are saved to the database. This was done by overriding the DbContext SaveChanges method and publishing the changed entities to the event "pipeline." I have not implemented this system in any pages yet. You can get an instance of the event handler by injecting the EntityChangeEventBroker class into your class (like you would a provider) and call the instance's Subscribe method passing an Action (method). The passed method will be executed on Entity changes saved with a list of the changed entities passed to the method. See the example in App.xaml.cs for details.

Please feel free to comment with any questions or ideas on how to better implement this. I would like to work with someone on Frontend/backend to see how we could wire this up in a view and test it with actual data changes.

title: Implemented configuration using the Microsoft.Extensions.Hosting package
body:
We will no longer be using resource files for configuration. The appsettings.json file will now hold any settings (such as database connection strings) that will be used during development.

**In order to use the project after this change**, you will need to make a copy of the appsettings-template.json file and rename it appsettings.json. This appsettings.json file should be ignored in git so it wont be committed to the git repo nor will your version of the file be overridden by other's changes.

I was bored so thought I'd pitch in my 2 cents.

I removed the "DesignTimeApplicationDBContext" and added the appsettings.json to the UI project.
